He wasn't supposed to hear this, but he is very glad he did. // END

"Go and get the drinks," Kyioomi calls out over his shoulder with an affectionate glare before he lets himself into Atsumu's flat, closes the door behind him and collapses against it with a loud sigh.

Only then Kyioomi realises he is still wearing his mask, but there is no point in letting his composure waver now and so he deftly pries the keys from Atsumu's hand and pushes past him, ignoring his shocked face that has turned from pink to a bright red.

Suddenly Kyoomi's hand is on Atsumu's cheek gently forcing the smaller man to look at him.
"But I did, so you better not chicken out now, Miya," he leans in, and presses a quick and chaste kiss to the tip of Atsumu's nose.

With a hand on the railing, Atsumu finally lets go of Kyioomi's sweater, his eyes looking everywhere but at the man in front of him. And it is so unlike Atsumu to avoid Kyoomi's attention that he can't help himself.

"Ya weren't supposed to hear this" his voice is breathless.
